description:
One of the oldest plant-based food establishments in the Philippines is Harvesterâ€™s Vegetarian. And you can find them at the food court of SM Megamall Mandaluyong. Back then, the restaurant was called Bodhi. It also used to carry a lot of vegetarian dishes, but now almost everything is vegan except for one noodle dish. 

My friend and I went here after my cooking demo. Tired and hungry, I was ready to eat a feast. Good thing they have combo meals, and they are super cheap! It even comes with an option of soup or drinks (we chose soup!) 

Seeing a plant-based stall at a mall food court is refreshing and heartwarming. Usually, nothing is vegan at mall food courts in the Philippines. And not only Harvesters is changing that, theyâ€™ve been changing that! Being in business for so long, theyâ€™ve withstood competing against a sea of meat-heavy stalls. And although their food looks like meat, their name proudly identifies them as meatless. So Iâ€™m very glad to support this Filipino Vegan OG!
